metadata.name: Tarantula Nebula
metadata.description:
Tarantula Nebula is an HII region (where hydrogen atoms ionized and glow in 656.3 nm wavelength red) within the Large Magellanic Cloud was first observed by Nicolas-Louis de Lacaille during an expedition to the Cape of Good Hope between 1751 and 1753.

Our home galaxy Milkyway has two satellite galaxies; the Large and the Small Magellanic Clouds. They are visible to the unaided eye in the Southern Hemisphere.

Image Credits: Mustafa AYDIN / Telescope Live
